article.headline: Air Force 72, CS Northridge 63
article.story: AIR FORCE ACADEMY, Colo. -- Tom Fow scored a season-high 22 points, and Air Force's defense held Cal State Northridge to 34 percent shooting in a 72-63 victory on Thursday night Fow made 4 of 8 3-point attempts for the Falcons (4-1). Todd Fletcher had 15 points and Taylor Brockhuis 12 for Air Force, which won its third straight. The Falcons' zone defense forced 19 turnovers. Rashaun McLemore had 18 points for Cal State Northridge (2-5), which is winless in three road games. Lennie Daniel had 16 points and 15 rebounds for the second double-double of the season and the 10th of his career.
